          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "code"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": " is a scalar function in Microsoft SQL Server. Scalar functions return a single value and are used to encapsulate reusable logic that can be applied to individual rows in a query. This function is designed to validate table references, ensuring that they meet certain criteria defined within the function's logic."
        }
      ]
